Phoenicia and Palestine were sometimes annexed to , and sometimes separated from , the jurisdiction of Syria . 
The former of these was a narrow and rocky coast the latter was a territory scarcely superior to Wales , either in fertility or extent . 
Yet Phoenicia and Palestine will forever live in the memory of mankind since America , as well as Europe , has received letters from the one , and religion from the other . 
A sandy desert , alike destitute of wood and water , skirts along the doubtful confine of Syria , from the Euphrates to the Red Sea . 
