The narrow policy of preserving , without any foreign mixture , the pure blood of the ancient citizens , had checked the fortune , and hastened the ruin , of Athens and Sparta . 
During the most flourishing aera of the Athenian commonwealth , the number of citizens gradually decreased from about thirty to twenty one thousand . 
When the allies of Rome claimed an equal share of honors and privileges , the senate indeed preferred the chance of arms to an ignominious concession . 
Under a democratical government , the citizens exercise the powers of sovereignty and those powers will be first abused , and afterwards lost , if they are committed to an unwieldy multitude . 
The Orbis Romanus of the learned Spanheim is a complete history of the progressive admission of Latium , Italy , and the provinces , to the freedom of Rome . 
