The right of Latium , as it was called , conferred on the cities to which it had been granted , a more partial favor . 
The grandsons of the Gauls , who had besieged Julius Caesar in Alcsia , commanded legions , governed provinces , and were admitted into the senate of Rome . 
Their ambition , instead of disturbing the tranquillity of the state , was intimately connected with its safety and greatness . 
