The princes who by their birth or their adoption belonged to the family of the Caesars , took the name of Caesar . 
After the death of Nero , this name designated the Imperial dignity itself , and afterwards the appointed successor . 
The time at which it was employed in the latter sense , cannot be fixed with certainty . 
