The custom passed from the theatre to the forum , from the forum to the senate . 
Applauses on the adoption of the Imperial decrees were first introduced under Trajan . 
One senator read the form of the decree , and all the rest answered by acclamations , accompanied with a kind of chant or rhythm . 
These were some of the acclamations addressed to Pertinax , and against the memory of Commodus . 
