The power of the sword is more sensibly felt in an extensive monarchy , than in a small community . 
It has been calculated by the ablest politicians , that no state , without being soon exhausted , can maintain above the hundredth part of its members in arms and idleness . 
But although this relative proportion may be uniform , the influence of the army over the rest of the society will vary according to the degree of its positive strength . 
The advantages of military science and discipline cannot be exerted , unless a proper number of soldiers are united into one body , and actuated by one soul . 
But after fifty years of peace and servitude , Tiberius ventured on a decisive measure , which forever rivetted the fetters of his country . 
