Though the three historians agree that it was in fact an auction , Herodian alone affirms that it was proclaimed as such by the soldiers . 
This infamous offer , the most insolent excess of military license , diffused a universal grief , shame , and indignation throughout the city . 
It reached at length the ears of Didius Julianus , a wealthy senator , who , regardless of the public calamities , was indulging himself in the luxury of the table . 
His wife and his daughter , his freedmen and his parasites , easily convinced him that he deserved the throne , and earnestly conjured him to embrace so fortunate an opportunity . 
The vain old man hastened to the Praetorian camp , where Sulpicianus was still in treaty with the guards , and began to bid against him from the foot of the rampart . 
The unworthy negotiation was transacted by faithful emissaries , who passed alternately from one candidate to the other , and acquainted each of them with the offers of his rival . 
