This melancholy truth was felt and acknowledged by Severus . 
Fortune and merit had , from an humble station , elevated him to the first place among mankind . 
The desire of perpetuating the greatness of his family was the only remaining wish of his ambition and paternal tenderness . 
Omnia fui , et nihil expedit . 
He had lost his first wife , while he was governor of the Lionnese Gaul . 
