W. The crime went not unpunished . 
The consciousness of his crime should have induced him to convince mankind , by the virtues of his reign , that the bloody deed had been the involuntary effect of fatal necessity . 
But the repentance of Caracalla only prompted him to remove from the world whatever could remind him of his guilt , or recall the memory of his murdered brother . 
On his return from the senate to the palace , he found his mother in the company of several noble matrons , weeping over the untimely fate of her younger son . 
