Note Valois and Reimar have explained in a very simple and probable manner this passage of Dion , which Gibbon seems to me not to have understood . 
He ordered that the soldiers should receive , as the reward of their services the Praetorians drachms , the other drachms . 
Valois thinks that the numbers have been transposed , and that Caracalla added drachms to the donations made to the Praetorians , to those of the legionaries . 
The Praetorians , in fact , always received more than the others . 
Augustus had settled that the Praetorians , after sixteen campaigns , should receive drachms the legionaries received only after twenty years . 
Caracalla added drachms to the donative of the Praetorians , to that of the legionaries . 
A secret conspiracy , provoked by his own jealousy , was fatal to the tyrant . 
The Praetorian praefecture was divided between two ministers . 
But his favor varied with the caprice of the emperor , and his life might depend on the slightest suspicion , or the most casual circumstance . 
