The colors of Roman marbles have been faintly described and imperfectly distinguished . 
It appears , however , that the Carystian was a sea green , and that the marble of Synnada was white mixed with oval spots of purple . 
He sometimes gave five hundred pair of gladiators , never less than one hundred and fifty . 
