Mithra is the first of the genii , or jzeds , created by Ormuzd it is he who watches over all nature . 
Hence arose the misapprehension of some of the Greeks , who have said that Mithra was the summus deus of the Persians he has a thousand ears and ten thousand eyes . 
The Chaldeans appear to have assigned him a higher rank than the Persians . 
It is he who bestows upon the earth the light of the sun . 
is thus an inferior genius , who , with many other genii , bears a part in the functions of Mithra . 
These assistant genii to another genius are called his kamkars but in the Zendavesta they are never confounded . 
It is probably this which has sometimes caused them to be confounded but Anquetil had himself exposed this error , which Kleuker , and all who have studied the Zendavesta , have noticed . 
