Hyde de Religione Persarum , c . 
The Magi , or sacerdotal order , were extremely numerous , since , as we have already seen , fourscore thousand of them were convened in a general council . 
Their forces were multiplied by discipline . 
The property of the Magi was very considerable . 
Besides the less invidious possession of a large tract of the most fertile lands of Media , they levied a general tax on the fortunes and the industry of the Persians . 
To obtain the acceptation of this guide to salvation , you must faithfully pay him tithes of all you possess , of your goods , of your lands , and of your money . 
If the destour be satisfied , your soul will escape hell tortures you will secure praise in this world and happiness in the next . 
For the destours are the teachers of religion they know all things , and they deliver all men . 
Hyde de Religione Persarum , c . 
