And yet , as the most philosophic minds can seldom refrain from investigating the infancy of great nations , our curiosity consumes itself in toilsome and disappointed efforts . 
When Tacitus considered the purity of the German blood , and the forbidding aspect of the country , he was disposed to pronounce those barbarians Indigence , or natives of the soil . 
To assert those savages to have been the spontaneous production of the earth which they inhabited would be a rash inference , condemned by religion , and unwarranted by reason . 
The emigration of the Gauls followed the course of the Danube , and discharged itself on Greece and Asia . 
Tacitus could discover only one inconsiderable tribe that retained any traces of a Gallic origin . 
