M. Notwithstanding the mysterious obscurity of the Edda , we can easily distinguish two persons confounded under the name of Odin the god of war , and the great legislator of Scandinavia . 
The latter , the Mahomet of the North , instituted a religion adapted to the climate and to the people . 
The faith that he had propagated , during a long and prosperous life , he confirmed by a voluntary death . 
Apprehensive of the ignominious approach of disease and infirmity , he resolved to expire as became a warrior . 
