M. Decius found the Goths engaged before Nicopolis , one of the many monuments of Trajan's victories . 
The camp of the Romans was surprised and pillaged , and , for the first time , their emperor fled in disorder before a troop of half armed barbarians . 
After a long resistance , Philoppopolis , destitute of succor , was taken by storm . 
A hundred thousand persons are reported to have been massacred in the sack of that great city . 
The time , however , consumed in that tedious siege , enabled Decius to revive the courage , restore the discipline , and recruit the numbers of his troops . 
Encouraged by the return of fortune , he anxiously waited for an opportunity to retrieve , by a great and decisive blow , his own glory , and that of the Roman arms . 
