The Goths were now , on every side , surrounded and pursued by the Roman arms . 
The flower of their troops had perished in the long siege of Philippopolis , and the exhausted country could no longer afford subsistence for the remaining multitude of licentious barbarians . 
Reduced to this extremity , the Goths would gladly have purchased , by the surrender of all their booty and prisoners , the permission of an undisturbed retreat . 
The high spirited barbarians preferred death to slavery . 
An obscure town of Maesia , called Forum Terebronii , was the scene of the battle . 
The Gothic army was drawn up in three lines , and either from choice or accident , the front of the third line was covered by a morass . 
The conflict was terrible it was the combat of despair against grief and rage . 
The barbarians , on the contrary , were inured to encounter in the bogs , their persons tall , their spears long , such as could wound at a distance . 
In this morass the Roman army , after an ineffectual struggle , was irrecoverably lost nor could the body of the emperor ever be found . 
