The Rhine , though dignified with the title of Safeguard of the provinces , was an imperfect barrier against the daring spirit of enterprise with which the Franks were actuated . 
Their rapid devastations stretched from the river to the foot of the Pyrenees nor were they stopped by those mountains . 
Spain , which had never dreaded , was unable to resist , the inroads of the Germans . 
During twelve years , the greatest part of the reign of Gallie nus , that opulent country was the theatre of unequal and destructive hostilities . 
