The splendid buildings of Antioch , private as well as public , were either pillaged or destroyed and the numerous inhabitants were put to the sword , or led away into captivity . 
The tide of devastation was stopped for a moment by the resolution of the high priest of Emesa . 
Demosthenes commanded in the place , not so much by the commission of the emperor , as in the voluntary defence of his country . 
