Several of the pretenders , who raised the standard of rebellion against the emperor Gallienus , were shining models of virtue , and almost all possessed a considerable share of vigor and ability . 
Their merit had recommended them to the favor of Valerian , and gradually promoted them to the most important commands of the empire . 
In times of confusion , every active genius finds the place assigned him by nature in a general state of war , military merit is the road to glory and to greatness . 
Of the nineteen tyrants Tetricus only was a senator Piso alone was a noble . 
The personal qualities of Piso added new lustre to his race . 
