The seven hills of Rome had been surrounded , by the successors of Romulus , with an ancient wall of more than thirteen miles . 
The vast enclosure may seem disproportioned to the strength and numbers of the infant state . 
But it was necessary to secure an ample extent of pasture and arable land , against the frequent and sudden incursions of the tribes of Latium , the perpetual enemies of the republic . 
It was a great but a melancholy labor , since the defence of the capital betrayed the decline of the monarchy . 
Of the seven hills , the Capitoline and Palatine only , with the adjacent valleys , were the primitive habitations of the Roman people . 
