The Roman people , says Aurelian , in an original letter , speak with contempt of the war which I am waging against a woman . 
They are ignorant both of the character and of the power of Zenobia . 
It is impossible to enumerate her warlike preparations , of stones , of arrows , and of every species of missile weapons . 
Every part of the walls is provided with two or three balistoe and artificial fires are thrown from her military engines . 
The fear of punishment has armed her with a desperate courage . 
Yet still I trust in the protecting deities of Rome , who have hitherto been favorable to all my undertakings . 
