But in the age of Tacitus , the coin had lost much of its weight and purity . 
After his accession , he gave orders that ten copies of the historian should be annually transcribed and placed in the public libraries . 
The Roman libraries have long since perished , and the most valuable part of Tacitus was preserved in a single Ms. , and discovered in a monastery of Westphalia . 
