It should seem that very many of those institutions , referred by an easy solution to the feudal system , are derived from the Celtic barbarians . 
When Caesar subdued the Gauls , that great nation was already divided into three orders of men the clergy , the nobility , and the common people . 
The first governed by superstition , the second by arms , but the third and last was not of any weight or account in their public councils . 
