In pursuance of their promise , the emperors soon afterwards appointed Sicorius Probus , one of their secretaries , to acquaint the Persian court with their final resolution . 
Three persons only assisted at this important conference , the minister Apharban , the praefect of the guards , and an officer who had commanded on the Armenian frontier . 
