M. Maxentius was the son of the emperor Maximian , and he had married the daughter of Galerius . 
The policy of Galerius preferred such associates as would never disgrace the choice , nor dispute the commands , of their benefactor . 
At the request of his son and of the senate , he condescended to reassume the purple . 
His ancient dignity , his experience , and his fame in arms , added strength as well as reputation to the party of Maxentius . 
