The fleet was composed of three hundred and fifty galleys of three ranks of oars . 
A hundred and thirty of these were furnished by Egypt and the adjacent coast of Africa . 
The troops of Constantine were ordered to a rendezvous at Thessalonica they amounted to above a hundred and twenty thousand horse and foot . 
Their emperor was satisfied with their martial appearance , and his army contained more soldiers , though fewer men , than that of his eastern competitor . 
But the naval preparations of Constantine were in every respect much inferior to those of Licinius . 
