The success of the Gnostics was rapid and extensive . 
They covered Asia and Egypt , established themselves in Rome , and sometimes penetrated into the provinces of the West . 
Though they constantly disturbed the peace , and frequently disgraced the name , of religion , they contributed to assist rather than to retard the progress of Christianity . 
Their faith was insensibly fortified and enlarged , and the church was ultimately benefited by the conquests of its most inveterate enemies . 
