But we may define , in a few words , the narrow limits of their original jurisdiction , which was chiefly of a spiritual , though in some instances of a temporal nature . 
These powers , during a short period , were exercised according to the advice of the presbyteral college , and with the consent and approbation of the assembly of Christians . 
The primitive bishops were considered only as the first of their equals , and the honorable servants of a free people . 
